    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Axes of the Late Bronze Age, successors to winged axes, with an eyelet to the side to fasten the blade and a recess at the top to better keep the handle in place.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
